linux:

install raylib using these instructions:

https://github.com/raysan5/raylib/wiki/Working-on-GNU-Linux

open a terminal and change directories to the psychosis directory then type:

make

-------------------

Windows:

if you have not done so already, download and install MinGW and make sure the MinGW
tools are in your PATH environment variable (look up the PATH environment variable
if you do not know what I am talking about):

http://mingw.org/

download the psychosis source code from here by clicking "clone or download":

https://github.com/stormchaser3000/psychosis

download a windows raylib (2.0.0 MinGW for simplicity) build from here:

https://github.com/raysan5/raylib/releases

and the Physac source code from here:

https://github.com/victorfisac/Physac/releases

unzip the three files into the same directory

run cmd.exe and use the cd command to change to the unzipped psychosis folder

example: cd Desktop\psychosis-build\psychosis

now type:

make.bat build

then go to the unzipped raylib folder and then the lib folder. copy libraylib_shared.dll
to the psychosis folder
